Tutorial Example: "Global Ocean State Estimation"
(Global Ocean State Estimation at 4 degree resolution)
=================================================

Configure and compile the code:
  cd build
  ../../../tools/genmake2 -oad -mods ../code_oad
  make adAll
  cd ..

To run:
  cp -r input_oad/ scratch/
  cd scratch
  ./prepare_run
  cd ..

  cp build/mitgcmuv_ad scratch/
  cp ../../../optim_m1qn3/src/optim.x scratch/

  To run once: make directory mitgcmtemp in /dev/shm
  oadcachedir=/dev/shm/mitgcmtemp/ ./mitgcmuv_ad
  OR
  To optimize: copy run_optim.py to scratch/
  python3 run_optim.py

  To visualise output:
  increment in xx_hfluxm.00000... meta/data files
  gradient in adxx_hfluxm.00000... meta/data files

  Copy files with cp scratch/xx_hfluxm* scratch/adxx_hfluxm* matlab/
  Use rdmds.m in utils/matlab, e.g.
  A = rdmds('xx_hfluxm.0000000001');A(A==0.0)=NaN;z=imagesc(A');set(z,'alphadata',~isnan(A));axis("xy");colorbar;
